  "teaching_materials": {
    "lesson_flow": [],
    "notes_on_text": [
      {
        "title": "1. was covered with...,覆盖着……。",
        "content": "This phrase describes something being completely covered by another thing. It's a common passive structure."
      },
      {
        "title": "2. What I saw made me very sad. 句中的主语 what I saw 是一个以what 引导的名词性从句。",
        "content": "The clause 'what I saw' functions as the subject of the sentence. 'What' introduces a noun clause, meaning 'the thing that'."
      },
      {
        "title": "3. I found a sign which said... 这里用 said 不当“说”讲,而是“写着……”。",
        "content": "In this context, 'said' is used to mean 'read' or 'had written on it', referring to the text on the sign, not spoken words."
      }
    ],
    "grammar_sections": [
      {
        "title": "Present Perfect Passive Voice",
        "explanation": "The present perfect passive voice is formed with 'has/have been' + past participle. It is used to describe an action that happened at an unspecified time in the past, or an action that started in the past and continues to the present, with emphasis on the result. In Lesson 144, it's used to ask if something has been done yet, e.g., 'Hasn't anyone repaired this car yet?'",
        "examples": [
          "It has already been repaired.",
          "They have already been corrected."
        ]
      },
      {
        "title": "Future Passive Voice",
        "explanation": "The future passive voice is formed with 'will be' + past participle. It is used to describe an action that will be done to the subject in the future. In Lesson 144, it's used to state that something will be done soon, e.g., 'It will be repaired soon!'",
        "examples": [
          "It will be repaired soon!",
          "They will be caught soon!"
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  "explanation_plan": {
